# STL Files Directory

Place your 3D model STL files here:

- `frame_base.stl` - Main base frame (mounting point for pan servo)
- `pan_platform.stl` - Rotating platform for pan servo
- `tilt_arm.stl` - Arm controlled by tilt servo
- `camera_bracket.stl` - USB camera and depth sensor mount
- `laser_mount.stl` - Laser module attachment

## Export to STL

### From FreeCAD
1. Select body/part in model tree
2. File → Export → Select `.stl` format
3. Choose "ASCII" or "Binary" (Binary is smaller)

### From Fusion 360
1. Right-click component
2. Save as STL
3. Select mesh refinement level

### From OpenSCAD
1. View → Render
2. Design → Export as STL

## Verify Before Printing

- [ ] All parts exported as binary STL (smaller files)
- [ ] No overlapping geometry
- [ ] Scale correct (measure one dimension)
- [ ] Surfaces are solids (no holes)
- [ ] Wall thickness adequate (>2mm)
